
Stone Poem is one of many public Campus Art pieces. This sculpture was made by Steve Gillman in the 1980s. The core group of stones were originally exhibited in the Nelson Gallery Richard L. Nelson Gallery during April  May 1986. Before erecting the sculpture as public art on campus, it was in the artists Oakland studio at the time of the 1989 wiki:WikiPedia:Loma_Prieta_earthquake Loma Prieta Earthquake . Several of the stones were knocked over and broken as a result of the quake and were reincorporated as benches benches on the perimeter of the UC Davis site. Stone Poem is located east of South Silo and south of the Bike Barn. To the north are the Chem mounds.


